OmniScript Group Elements

Block: The Block element groups elements inside of a Step component into a manageable structure.

Edit Block: The Edit Block element groups together inputs to allow users to add, edit, and delete records.

Filter Block: The Filter Block is the container that holds Filters.

Input Block: The Input Block acts as a placeholder for a custom template.

Radio Group: The Radio Group element allows users to quickly answer a large volume of multiple choice questions in one step.

Selectable Items: The Selectable Items component uses an array to populate a list of selectable items.

Step: The Step element divides the OmniScript into different sections.

Type Ahead Block: The Type Ahead Block displays as a text input field; the field auto completes results based on the user's input.

Action Block: Run multiple OmniScript Actions asynchronously by grouping them in an Action Block. Actions within the Action Block run in parallel and inherit the Action Block's settings.

Block: The Block element groups elements inside of a Step component into a manageable structure.

Edit Block: The Edit Block element groups together inputs to allow users to add, edit, and delete records.

Action Block
Run multiple OmniScript Actions asynchronously by grouping them in an Action Block. Actions within the Action Block run in parallel and inherit the Action Block's settings.
Block
Combine logical groups of elements in an OmniScript Step using a Block element.
Edit Block
Create, edit, and delete multiple Salesforce or external records on one page using Edit Block. For example, if you are collecting an Account's Contact information, you can add an Edit Block to your OmniScript to enable users to add a record for each Contact.
Radio Group
OmniScript's Radio Group enables you to create and display questions in a questionnaire format.
Steps
Each Step element in an OmniScript presents a page to the user that prompts for input or displays information. For navigation, all Steps except the first have a Next button, and all except the last have a Previous button.
Type Ahead Block
Display a list of results when a user begins typing in an input field by using the Type Ahead Block. When a user selects a record, the Type Ahead Block can retrieve additional information related to the record. For example, a Type Ahead Block can be used with an Omnistudio Data Mapper to list Accounts in the results.
